Channels

Channels are named state variables that drive app behavior. Each channel is a tiddler in the wiki store.

State tiddler path:

```
$:/state/rimir/statewrap/<appTitle>/<channelName>
```

The `text` field holds the current value. Empty text = channel is unset.

Reading channels in wikitext:

Inside view tiddlers (which are wrapped by `<$statewrap>`), use these filter operators:

- `[statewrap-get[project]]` — returns current value of the "project" channel
- `[statewrap-ref[project]]` — returns the full state tiddler path (useful for `$reveal stateTitle`)

Example: `<%if [statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]]%>...<%endif%>`

Setting a channel value:

From outside (tool call):
```
set_field(title="$:/state/rimir/statewrap/<appTitle>/<channel>", field="text", value="new value")
```

From wikitext (inside a button or action):
```
<$action-statewrap-set channel="project" value="Alpha"/>
```

To clear: set value to empty string `""`.

Adding a new channel:

1. Read the app tiddler's `appify-channels` field
2. Append the new channel name (space-separated)
3. set_field to update `appify-channels`
4. Optionally set a default: set_field(field="appify-default-<channelName>", value="default")

Example — add a "theme" channel with default "light":
```
set_field(title="<appTitle>", field="appify-channels", value="project task tab theme")
set_field(title="<appTitle>", field="appify-default-theme", value="light")
```

Removing a channel:

1. Remove the name from `appify-channels`
2. Delete the `appify-default-<channel>` field if it exists (set to empty)
3. Consider removing rules that reference it

See also: llm_help("appify/rules") — reactive rules that fire when channels change
